text: Gulnoza Matniyazova (born August 10, 1994) is an Uzbekistani judoka. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 70 kg event, in which she was eliminated in the first round by Katarzyna Kłys. At the 2019 Asian-Pacific Judo Championships held in Fujairah, United Arab Emirates, she won the silver medal in the women's 70 kg event. In the women's 70 kg event at the 2019 Military World Games held in Wuhan, China, she also won one of the bronze medals. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Uzbekistani female judoka Category:Olympic judoka of Uzbekistan Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Judoka at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Judoka at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Judoka at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Uzbekistan Category:Asian Games medalists in judo Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games
